<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="id13a5b1b3-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d" identifier="/us/usc/t21/s147"><num value="147">§ 147.</num><heading> Repeal of inconsistent laws</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Any laws or parts of laws inconsistent with this subchapter are repealed.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="id13a5b1b4-3a70-11f1-b089-c1e1e512a22d">(<ref href="/us/act/1927-02-15/ch155/s7">Feb. 15, 1927, ch. 155, § 7</ref>, <ref href="/us/stat/44/1103">44 Stat. 1103</ref>.)</sourceCredit>
